A Toyota Sienna vehicle conveying members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) from Abuja to Port Harcourt after the party’s convention has tumbled killing one person and injuring five others. An occupant of the ill-fated vehicle, Innocent Amadi, announced the development on Thursday while speaking to a popular radio station in Port Harcourt. He said the accident happened around 8am on Thursday near the University of Abuja Staff quarters. He said the vehicle’s driver was on high speed when he suddenly applied the brakes after sighting another vehicle in front.   Terrorist kill 32 in four Kaduna communities     Tinubu condoles Rivers APC over death of delegate     APC Primary: Be magnanimous in victory, Jimoh Ibrahim urges…   He said: “Our vehicle was on high speed. So, in the process there was another vehicle before him. “Because he was on high speed, he couldn’t control, he applied the breaks and the wheeled pulled out. “The motor summersaulted. I was in front of the vehicle. I came out unhurt. I fastened my seal belt. Though we lost one person. Five persons were injured”.